# Read the Excel file into a pandas DataFrame

# Now 'df' contains your data, and you can perform various operations on it
print(pdf)

llon=pdf['Long'].min()-0.03
ulon=pdf['Long'].max()+0.03

from mpl_toolkits.basemap import Basemap
from pylab import rcParams
import numpy as np

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.lines import Line2D
from matplotlib.patches import Patch

# Buat peta dasar
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 10))
my_map = Basemap(projection='merc', area_thresh = 1000.0,llcrnrlon=llon, llcrnrlat=llat, #min longitude (llcrnrlon) and latitude (llcrnrlat)
            urcrnrlon=ulon, urcrnrlat=ulat, epsg=4326) #max longitude (urcrnrlon) and latitude (urcrnrlat)
#my_map.drawcoastlines(color='gray')
#my_map.fillcontinents(color = 'white', alpha = 0.01)
my_map.arcgisimage(service='World_Shaded_Relief', xpixels = 1500, verbose= True)

parallels = np.arange(llat, ulat, 0.05)
my_map.drawparallels(parallels,labels=[True,False,False,False], color='#A9A9A9')
meridians = np.arange(llon, ulon, 0.05)
my_map.drawmeridians(meridians,labels=[False,False,False,True], color='#A9A9A9')


# Convert latitude and longitude to map coordinates
#x, y = my_map(pdf['Long'].values, pdf['Lat'].values)

x,y = my_map(np.asarray(pdf.Long), np.asarray(pdf.Lat))
pdf['xm']= x.tolist()
pdf['ym'] =y.tolist()

# Plot the data on the map


#c = plt.colorbar(orientation='vertical', shrink = 0.5)
#c.set_label("Kerapatan Gempabumi")

legend_elements = [#Line2D([0], [0], color='gray', lw=2, label='Garis Pantai'),
                   Line2D([0], [0], marker='^', color='w', label='Stasiun Seismograf',
                          markerfacecolor=([0, 0, 1]), markeredgecolor='blue', markersize=12)]

# Create the figure
plt.legend(handles=legend_elements, loc='upper right')
plt.title("Peta Stasiun dan Waveform")

for index, row in pdf.iterrows():
    my_map.plot(row.xm, row.ym, markerfacecolor =([0, 0, 1]), marker='^', markeredgecolor='blue', markersize= 12, alpha = 0.75)
#my_map.plot(x, y, markerfacecolor =([0, 0, 1]), markersize= 23, marker='^', alpha=0.75)


# Tentukan koordinat untuk menempatkan gambar
#for i in range(1,len(pdf['Lat']))
image_lat, image_lon = pdf['Lat'][0]+0.015, pdf['Long'][0]-0.015
image_lat1, image_lon1 = pdf['Lat'][1]+0.015, pdf['Long'][1]-0.015
image_lat2, image_lon2 = pdf['Lat'][2]+0.015, pdf['Long'][2]-0.015

# Masukkan gambar dengan ukuran lebih kecil

img_extent = [image_lon - 0.015, image_lon + 0.015, image_lat - 0.015, image_lat + 0.015]
ax.imshow(img, extent=img_extent, alpha=0.75)

image_path = '29.png'
img = plt.imread(image_path)

ax.imshow(img, extent=img_extent, alpha=0.75)
